## Part F — Code review and testing discipline

### 20. Simulation before real hardware — always

- Every new trajectory, planner change, or controller configuration must be
  tested in the Isaac Sim (or equivalent) environment first.
- Never merge code that has only been tested on real hardware without a
  corresponding simulation test that can be re-run in CI.

### 21. Incremental deployment with reduced limits

- When deploying new motion code to real hardware for the first time, use
  reduced velocity limits (e.g. 25% of normal) and a constrained workspace.
- Only increase limits after successful runs with an operator present and
  e-stop in hand.

### 22. Two-person rule for first-time real execution

- The first real execution of any new trajectory or planner behavior should
  have two people present: one operating the software, one with hand on the
  hardware e-stop.
- This rule can be relaxed for repeat runs of proven trajectories.

